<item>
            <title>[OAK-455] Caching in MongoMK</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-455</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, there&apos;s no caching at all in MongoMK. This makes MongoMK related tests very slow (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-440&quot; title=&quot;Concurrency issue when 3 microkernels are writing in the same db&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-440&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-440&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) as each node has to be read from MongoDB and that takes a while. We need some kind of caching in MongoMK and we need to make sure that it&apos;s cluster aware (i.e. if some other MongoMK changes something in the cache, the cache needs to somehow know about it and invalidate)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
